Enlisted Heritage: Where are you?<br><br>
I am currently enlisted in the USAF.  I am stationed at Keesler AFB, MS.  Currently, I am attending Airman Leadership School and attempting to do a research paper on the enlisted heritage of the USAF.  I have chosen Duane Hackney in a tribute to his selfless acts of bravery while in Vietnam.  It is very hard to find information on him even though he is one of the most highly decorated airmen in the history of the Air Force.  I have seen information on these pages, but have been unable to contact those who are writing .  If anyone can help me give due respect to one of your fellow heroes please contact me at the address below.<br><br>

